abstract: A federal judge handed Facebook a final victory in its lawsuit with ConnectU over who originated the social networking service, ending a turbulent chapter for the company.
snippet: A federal judge handed Facebook a final victory in its lawsuit with ConnectU over who originated the social networking service, ending a turbulent chapter for the company.
lead_paragraph: Facebook has finally closed the book on its long-running, multi-front legal battle with the rival college social network ConnectU — but not before a new question was raised about Facebook’s supposed $15 billion valuation.

headline.main: Judge Ends Facebook’s Feud With ConnectU
